Let's continue talking about Han Shangyan. Does he have a girlfriend or not?

479
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:10,650
- Teacher, I want to listen. May I?
- This, I don't know.

480
00:36:10,650 --> 00:36:14,090
- You can.
- You need to ask his old team. Han Shangyan isn't easy to get along with.

481
00:36:14,090 --> 00:36:16,620
He mixes well and he's a guy with an open heart.

482
00:36:16,620 --> 00:36:19,640
But most people are only nodding acquaintances.

483
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:24,000
Yet, this is fine, too: he's reassuring to people, he doesn't smooth-talk people with slickness.

484
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:26,610
Then, what about now?

485
00:36:26,610 --> 00:36:28,430
Now?

486
00:36:28,430 --> 00:36:32,190
Does he have anyone that he is seeing right now?

487
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,570
Probably.

488
00:36:33,570 --> 00:36:34,900
- He does?
- He does?

489
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:38,380
Our company had a girl before who kept pursuing him.

490
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:43,220
But I heard an insider from K&K say that Han Shangyan seems to have a girlfriend.

491
00:36:43,220 --> 00:36:44,910
When did that happen?

492
00:36:44,910 --> 00:36:47,560
Probably in the past few days? I'd never heard about it before.

493
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:50,520
It must have just started recently. It seems pretty mysterious.

494
00:36:50,520 --> 00:36:52,390
Nobody knows.

495
00:36:58,590 --> 00:37:00,990
Say, this guy is really heartless.

496
00:37:00,990 --> 00:37:05,200
He just broke up with you not too long ago. Not even a few days?

497
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:06,690
Two weeks.

498
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:11,570
Two weeks? I hate this type the most! You just broke up and he already found the next one.

499
00:37:11,570 --> 00:37:14,930
Say, didn't he go through any moment of sad transition?

500
00:37:14,930 --> 00:37:19,080
If you ask me, in the last period, he put no heart in it.

501
00:37:20,930 --> 00:37:23,120
And I thought he was a pretty good person, too!

502
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:28,650
When I go home, first I'll give a beating to my hubby to vent my anger, that'll teach him to be a fan of such an idol.

503
00:37:31,060 --> 00:37:35,570
Little Squid, I urge you to just give up.

504
00:37:52,150 --> 00:37:56,790
<i> We worked together with several top students from a research lab in Jiaodong University to finish this project.</i>

505
00:37:56,790 --> 00:38:00,500
Jiaodong University? Isn't that Nian Nian's university?

506
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:03,070
<i> [Officer Li: They're helping our city's investigative team with a facial recognition software.]</i>

507
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:04,970
I think it is.

508
00:38:06,940 --> 00:38:09,700
This granddaughter-in-law I have is just like you!

509
00:38:09,700 --> 00:38:13,680
She's a genius! A high technology genius!

510
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:18,150
Nian Nian hasn't come in a long time, has she?

511
00:38:18,150 --> 00:38:19,420
Yeah.

512
00:38:19,420 --> 00:38:21,410
Why is that?

513
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,670
I don't know.

514
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:27,140
Little Bai. Child, you have never been a liar, since you were little.

515
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:29,980
Tell me quickly. Why is that?

516
00:38:30,870 --> 00:38:33,030
You should ask my bro instead.

517
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:34,860
I'm asking you!

518
00:38:36,300 --> 00:38:39,690
I think... there's a bit of a problem.

519
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:43,510
